{
  "texts": [
    "The HF Hamiltonian on the fine mesh is then diagonalized to obtain the mean-field band structure.",
    "Since this calculation only needs to be performed once after the final iteration, it does not add significantly to the computational cost.",
    "Shell-filling EffectsOne type of finite-size effect that can be significant in HF calculations is related to \"shell-filling\".",
    "For example, even if the ground state in the thermodynamic limit should be a spin-unpolarized state, a HF calculation with an odd number of electrons necessarily yields a spin imbalance of at least one.",
    "A finite-size HF solution may thus break certain symmetries that would in fact be preserved in the thermodynamic limit."
  ]
}